f being protected by powerful magiks.<br><br>The only one powerful enough to be protecting him is a level 63+ enchanter in the city named Nathyn Illuminous, though this person's true identity, he claims, is Tsaph Katta. To prove this, you must have a rogue (not sure on skill needed, greater than 100, I used 200) open the a door in the home of Nathyn, (small castle structure, high nothern part of the zone, due north from the ramp exit from the lower area) where there is a book sitting on a table. Warning a mid-level vampire spawns when you open the door, should be no problem if you're doing this quest though. Returning this book to Abrogast yeilds no information -  Nathyn is too smart to leave such evidence lying around.<br><br>At this point Abrogast tells you the biggest secret yet - Norrath is an illusion. I quote:<br>&quot;That large blue orb that hangs in the Luclin sky from time to time is nothing more than an<br>overgrown comet. What appear to be land masses and other geological features are<br>actually powerful illusions cast upon the comet by Tsaph Katta imself so that panic does<br>not spread amongst the ignorant masses. I am not one to spread conjecture, but it is<br>possible that Katta's astronomers have discovered that the comet is hurling slowly toward<br>Luclin and will destroy all life on the planet, so you can see why he would keep the truth<br>about the [Exodus] from his journal.&quot;<br><br>In your SoL manual you can read up on the Exodus. He now sends you to prove that the<br>Exodus never took place. To prove this you must travel to the greatest Library known to<br>Luclin - the great library in the casters guild of Shadow Haven. You will see, there is little<br>information to prove the Exodus happened. Talk to a librarian (not necissary to complete<br>the quest) and she will tell you that an annoying gnome named Peqi checked out the only<br>book they have on the Exodus.<br><br>I spent many hours looking for Peqi in Shadow Haven. Finally, 2 minutes before<br>the servers came down &quot;Peqi Soandso begins to cast a spell.&quot; I finally found him but only<br>enough time to have a short dialoge. He is an extremely stuborn gnome who does not<br>want to give up his book - he says ONLY over his dead body. To find him, walk across the<br>bridge heading away from the library/caster/monk guild. Right as you step off the bridge,<br>turn right, walk foward, and open the second door on your right -- Peqi spawns infront of<br>the flower pot. Appears to be around 24 hrs spawn time. This is the quest bottleneck.<br><br>Peqi has little HP and hits for almost nothing though he is blue at level 60. He drops the book on the Exodus, and does not give a faction hit of any kind. Once you have the book, place it in the wrappings Abrogast provided and return it to him.<br><br>As he examines the book he leaves you thorougly convinced the book is not a forgery, and that he has been wrong all this time. But still, he wishes one more chance to prove these things to you, and if you do, he will give you a powerful cloak given to him by Suma himself. You must find 2 &quot;Akuel xi ans Vius&quot; and return them in another container. These items can be found on &quot;The Protector&quot; as well as other cloaked-figure looking NPC's in Ashevka zone, off of Maiden's.<br><br>Upon returning this to him, he and his friend Miller have an argument about how you were not supposed to make it back alive. But ok, they'll give you the item they promised, just come with them to the bank. At the bank they take out the item (which is in 2 seperate pieces) but also their weapons. They now inform you that they are going to keep their cloak - @#%$ off basically - and they walk back to the bar. <br><br>The fight with them is pretty easy, one is a 49 cleric, the other a 47 warrior. A 60 cleric and 60 war can handle it easily. Loot the small black necklace off of Abrogast and the heavy drape off of Miller. Combine the necklace with the drape and receieve your reward: Cloak of Truth. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usergex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sergex </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/12/01 4:40:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3484.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok, Ok... Cloak of Truth</span><hr size=1> @%#$! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utofuwoodelf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tofu wood elf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.webspawner.com/users/akmo/elffy.bmp" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/12/01 4:52:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3484.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Killing miller and Abrogast</span><hr size=1> Great info Treskin, thx =)<br><br>just wondering if we should kill them just inside the building? or we have to pull them a some spot with no other npcs?  Will the guards assist?<br><br>~Elf<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utreskin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Treskin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registere