uth for yourself? That is good, you will be taking your first step down a winding road to the only fulfillment this existence has to offer: enlightenment. Take this flask of water, I have blessed it such that it will singe the skin of the unholy. Go to Phenic Dionicas and give it to him, then you will see... you will see.<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:32:08 2001] Miller says 'Yeah, splash it right in his unliving face!<br><br>Give Arbogasts' holy water (sorry, didn't think to ID it) to Phenic.<br><br>[Tue Dec 11 20:36:35 2001] Phenic Dionicas looks at you and smiles despite the fact that you have splashed water all over him- he does not appear to be burning at all. 'Oh, excuse me. You seem to have spilled your water, here have some of mine my friend. Good day to you, Shariin,' he says.<br><br>He gives you a bottle of water back.<br><br>[Tue Dec 11 20:37:25 2001] Item Lore: Just plain old water.<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:39:00 2001] Arbogast says 'He simply gave this to you? Cunning indeed for him to cover his weakness so thoroughly- he must have powerful protective enchantments in place, no doubt put in place by his good friend and associate, Tsaph Katta!<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:39:00 2001] Your faction standing with The Truth got better.<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:39:00 2001] You gain experience!!<br><br>Arbogast gives you a 2-slot nodrop container called &quot;Silver wrappings&quot;.<br><br>[Tue Dec 11 20:33:54 2001] You say, 'who is tsaph katta?'<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:33:54 2001] Arbogast says 'When you fake your death to discredit another you only discredit yourself when another sees your death was faked. Yes, you heard me correctly, Tsaph Katta lives on here in this city, can you guess who it is he pretends to be?<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:33:54 2001] Miller says 'Ooh! I know, I know! Nathyn Illuminious!!!<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:33:54 2001] Arbogast says 'Yes, yes, I know you know... very good Miller<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:33:54 2001] Miller beams a smile your way.<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:32:34 2001] You say, 'who is nathyn?'<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:32:35 2001] Arbogast says 'Yes, wealthy philanthropist Nathyn Illuminious is simply a guise for the infamous Tsaph Katta, hiding in plain sight. Few are aware of this truth my friend, but no doubt, were you to acquire and peruse ''Nathyn's'' personal memoirs, you would see him for what he truly is. If you can find it, bring it to me, but do not hand it to me in plain sight- we would be wise not to call attention to our business. Wrap it up in that silver wrapping paper, as though you are bringing me a gift... yes, a gift.<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:33:17 2001] You say, 'who is nathyn?'<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:33:17 2001] Miller says 'Grrr that scoundrel, pretending to be someone he ain't! Why I oughtta?<br><br>Go to Nathyn's place, pick the lock and step inside.<br><br>[Tue Dec 11 18:54:25 2001] The study locks behind you... You get the feeling you<br>are not alone.<br><br>A Coterie Servant (well green to me) will spawn. Easy kill.<br><br>[Tue Dec 11 18:55:34 2001] Your faction standing with Coterie of the Eternal Night<br>got worse.<br>[Tue Dec 11 18:55:34 2001] Your faction standing with Validus Custodus got better.<br>[Tue Dec 11 18:55:34 2001] Your faction standing with Nathyn Illuminious got bette<br>r.<br>[Tue Dec 11 18:55:34 2001] Your faction standing with Valdanov Zevfeer got worse.<br><br>Grab Nathyn's Memoirs (nodrop) off the bedside table.<br><br>[Tue Dec 11 20:37:31 2001] Item Lore: Private.<br><br>And combine the book in your silver wrappings.<br><br>[Tue Dec 11 20:39:22 2001] You have fashioned the items together to create something new!<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:39:29 2001] Arbogast says, 'Ahh, you have retrieved the memoirs, let me see.' Arbogast opens the book and starts flipping through pages, 'Yes here, you... no, wait it must be back... hrmmm, maybe he... but it must... Well, that was pretty clever of old Tsaph Katta, removing any record of who he truly is- probably did it to cover up the fact that Norrath does not really exist.'<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:39:29 2001] Your faction standing with The Truth got better.<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:39:29 2001] You gain experience!!<br><br>Arbogast gives you &quot;Gold wrappings&quot;.<br><br>[Tue Dec 11 20:40:01 2001] You say, 'norrath does exist'<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:40:01 2001] Arbogast says 'You are beginning to see the truest truths as the only true truths now, are you not? That large blue orb that hangs in the Luclin sky from time to time is nothing more than an overgrown comet. What appear to be land masses and other geological features are in actuality powerful illusions cast upon the comet by Tsaph Katta himself so that panic does not spread amongst the ignorant masses. I am not one to spread conjecture, but it is possible that Katta's astronomers have discovered that the comet is hurtling slowly toward Luclin and will destroy all life on the planet, so you can see why he would want to keep the truth about the [Exodus] from his journal.<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:40:15 2001] You say, 'what exodus?'<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:40:15 2001] Arbogast says 'The Exodus is the single biggest lie propagated onto the people of Katta Castellum in the known history of the intelligent races. Hogwash I tell you.<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:40:15 2001] Miller says 'A bloody, boldfaced lie!<br>[Tue Dec 11 20:40:15 2001] Arbogast says 'A story told to children. Tsaph Katta wove together a tale of Seru trying to kill him on the fantasy world of ''Norrath'' and how the entire combine fled here to escape from him... a wheel of lies, do you see how they interconnect? Why, I'll bet that even in Shadowhaven, the very site of this alleged ''Exodus'' and home to one of the grandest libraries you will ever see, not a single shred of reliable evidence regarding such an event could be found. HA! You bring me a book on this ''Exodus'' and Miller here will eat his hat! Especially if the book is wrapped in that gold paper I gave you...<br><br>Go to the Library in Shadowhaven