e? Get out, no one invited you here, leave me be! Come back again and I'll call the guards. Go!<br>[Tue Dec 11 21:59:56 2001] You say, 'what book of exodus?'<br>[Tue Dec 11 21:59:56 2001] Peqi Biato says 'I have books, I have lots of books, books about the Exodus and all kinds of things but they're mine, you hear me? Mine! You'll get that book over my dead body, now get out! Out, I say!<br><br>Significant time gap here as I go LD several times, try to recruit help, etc. I eventually give up, pop duelist and miss my backstab. /sigh He barely scratched me, though (lots of misses, couple of hits for 80ish). Gotta love casters...<br><br>[Tue Dec 11 22:44:11 2001] Peqi Biato says '''Over my dead body'' is just an expression, I didn't want to have to hurt you but you brought it on yourself.<br>[Tue Dec 11 22:44:29 2001] Shariin ASSASSINATES their victim!!<br>[Tue Dec 11 22:44:29 2001] You backstab Peqi Biato for 32000 points of damage.<br>[Tue Dec 11 22:44:29 2001] You have slain Peqi Biato!<br>[Tue Dec 11 22:44:29 2001] You gain experience!!<br>[Tue Dec 11 22:44:29 2001] Peqi Biato's corpse dies as he lived, with a scowl on his tiny face.<br>[Tue Dec 11 22:44:41 2001] You receive 5 platinum, 8 gold, 9 silver, 10 copper from the corpse.<br>[Tue Dec 11 22:44:46 2001] --You have looted a The Exodus: A History.--<br><br>Combine the book in the wrappings.<br>[Tue Dec 11 22:45:05 2001] You have fashioned the items together to create something new!<br><br>And hand your gold-wrapped book in.<br>[Tue Dec 11 23:04:40 2001] Arbogast looks taken aback for a moment before collecting himself, 'Get your hat out of your mouth, Miller- this book is a fraud! It was clearly planted there by Tsaph Katta. Look at this, umm... handwriting! Yes, look at this handwriting. I have clearly underestimated his penchant for skullduggery.' Arbogast, completely sure of himself once again, leans in and speaks softly to you, 'Now that you have witnessed these clear, undeniable truths f