nd best times I've had in ages.<br><br>Starts out with me logging on around noon EST with my rogue and my 54th cleric (dark elf, and kos in Katta).  I run to Shadow Haven, wanting to get to Peqi before some guild decides to perma camp him for the next week.  A little over 7 hours later, and there's one dead gnome, and I loot the book.<br><br>I run off to Katta, and buff my rogue hoping to solo the mob behind the door, when lo and behold I run into a cleric friend of mine working on the quest, and stuck at the locked door.  (Hi Corinus.)  So, I help him out, and he helps me out.  I then do the book turn in step, and now have to get the parts from Akheva.<br><br>So, a quick check on my friends list, and a bunch from a larger guild are in Akheva at the moment, so I run out there, and hang out for a bit,a nd one of them hands me two Akuel xi ans Vius.  Combine them in the pouch, and I start the run back to Katta while trying to round up some guildmates for the final fight.  Most of the guild was on a general raid, but I got a 55 monk and 56 bard.  We all get out to Katta, and I buff them with the cleric, and we decide to try without a healer, since he's kos.  Didn't work too well, mezzed Miller (the warrior) first, and went after Abrogast since we wanted the healer dead.  With no real way to stop the cheals, things weren't looking too good, so we decided we had nothing to lose, and pulled them all the way to zone to fight where the cleric was.  We get Abrogast dead, and cleric is lom, so bard keeps Miller mezzed while twisting in mana regen.  Then, much to our surprise, the wandering Legionnaire got a bit close, and aggroed the cleric, and the bard.  Both zoned, and the monk and I were left alone to fight Miller.  Both of us used our riposte Discs, and he used his mend, I died, but thought ahead and had bound right there.  Cleric zoned back in in time to heal up the monk, but was still low mana.  Bard got back in, remezzed Miller, I looted my weapons, and we let the cleric get to 40 mana.  After that, Miller died quick, and I finished the quest.  Was really close, especially with the rediculous zone times now.  I'm glad I have everything turned off on the cleric, or he may not have zoned quick enough.  But, he now has his cloak.  =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=3484.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=3484.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=3484.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=3484.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=3484.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=3484.topic&start=121&stop=140>7</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=3484.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=3484.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3484.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3484.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3484.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topi